t(), None);"},{"DocComment":" ```"},{"DocComment":""},{"DocComment":" Because the closure passed to `filter()` takes a reference, and many"},{"DocComment":" iterators iterate over references, this leads to a possibly confusing"},{"DocComment":" situation, where the type of the closure is a double reference:"},{"DocComment":""},{"DocComment":" ```"},{"DocComment":" let s = &[0, 1, 2];"},{"DocComment":""},{"DocComment":" let mut iter = s.iter().filter(|x| **x > 1); // needs two *s!"},{"DocComment":""},{"DocComment":" assert_eq!(iter.next(), Some(&2));"},{"DocComment":" assert_eq!(iter.next(), None);"},{"DocComment":" ```"},{"DocComment":""},{"DocComment":" It's common to instead use destructuring on the argument to strip away one:"},{"DocComment":""},{"DocComment":" ```"},{"DocComment":" let s = &[0, 1, 2];"},{"DocComment":""},{"DocComment":" let mut iter = s.iter().filter(|&x| *x > 1); // both & and *"},{"DocComment":""},{"DocComment":" assert_eq!(iter.next(), Some(&2));"},{"DocComment":" assert_eq!(iter.next(), None);"},{"DocComment":" ```"},{"DocComment":""},{"DocComment":" or both:"},{"DocComment":""},{"DocComment":" ```"},{"DocComment":" let s = &[0, 1, 2];"},{"DocComment":""},{"DocComment":" let mut iter = s.iter().filter(|&&x| x > 1); // two &s"},{"DocComment":""},{"DocComment":" assert_eq!(iter.next(), Some(&2));"},{"DocComment":" assert_eq!(iter.next(), None);"},{"DocComment":" ```"},{"DocComment":""},{"DocComment":" of these layers."},{"DocComment":""},{"DocComment":" Note that `iter.filter(f).next()` is equivalent to `iter.find(f)`."},{"Unknown":{"path":"rustc_diagnostic_item","args":"\"iter_filter\""}}],"inline":"Hint","rename":null,"public":true},"is_local":false,"opacity":"Foreign","lang_item":"iter_filter"},"generics":{"regions":[],"types":[{"index":0,"name":"A"},{"index":1,"name":"P"}],"const_generics":[],"trait_clauses":[{"clause_id":0,"span":{"data":{"file_id":16,"beg":{"line":852,"col":8},"end":{"line":852,"col":12}},"generated_from_span":null},"ori